craterdog.collections.primitives

Class RandomizedTree<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • craterdog.collections.primitives.RandomizedTree<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of the elements in the tree.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<E>, Collection<E>

    public final class RandomizedTree<E>
extends AbstractCollection<E>
    This class provides an implementation of the randomized binary search tree (RBST). The approach was defined by CONRADO MART ́INEZ And SALVADOR ROURA in their paper published in Journal of the ACM, Vol. 45, No. 2, March 1998, pp. 288–323. It implements a standard binary search tree but uses random choices to keep the tree statically balanced after each insertion or deletion. All nodes in the tree have an equal probability of being the root node. This implementation is configurable such that it allows the programmer to specify whether or not duplicate entities are allowed in the tree.
    Author:
    Derk Norton
